ed character learn a spell of id #spell. If \'all\' provided then all ranks learned.'),(418,'Command: learn all','Syntax: .learn all $subcommand\r\nType .learn all to see the list of possible subcommands or .help learn all $subcommand to see info on subcommands'),(419,'Command: learn all my','Syntax: .learn all my $subcommand\r\nType .learn all my to see the list of possible subcommands or .help learn all my $subcommand to see info on subcommands'),(420,'Command: learn all my class','Syntax: .learn all my class\r\n\r\nLearn all spells and talents available for his class.'),(421,'Command: learn all my pettalents','Syntax: .learn all my pettalents\r\n\r\nLearn all talents for your pet available for his creature type (only for hunter pets).'),(422,'Command: learn all my spells','Syntax: .learn all my spells\r\n\r\nLearn all spells (except talents and spells with first rank learned as talent) available for his class.'),(423,'Command: learn all my talents','Syntax: .learn all my talents\r\n\r\nLearn all talents (and spells with first rank learned as talent) available for his class.'),(424,'Command: learn all gm','Syntax: .learn all gm\r\n\r\nLearn all default spells for Game Masters.'),(425,'Command: learn all crafts','Syntax: .learn crafts\r\n\r\nLearn all professions and recipes.'),(426,'Command: learn all default','Syntax: .learn all default [$playername]\r\n\r\nLearn for selected/$playername player all default spells for his race/class and spells rewarded by completed quests.'),(427,'Command: learn all lang','Syntax: .learn all lang\r\n\r\nLearn all languages'),(428,'Command: learn all recipes','Syntax: .learn all recipes [$profession]\r\rLearns all recipes of specified profession and sets skill level to max.\rExample: .learn all recipes enchanting'),(429,'Command: unlearn','Syntax: .unlearn #spell [all]\r\n\r\nUnlearn for selected player a spell #spell.  If \'all\' provided then all ranks unlearned.'),(430,'Command: lfg','Syntax: .lfg $subcommand\r\nType .lfg to see the list of possible subcommands or .help lfg $subcommand to see info on subcommands'),(431,'Command: lfg player','Syntax: .lfg player\n Shows information about player (state, roles, comment, dungeons selected).'),(432,'Command: lfg group','Syntax: .lfg group\n Shows information about all players in the group  (state, roles, comment, dungeons selected).'),(433,'Command: lfg queue','Syntax: .lfg queue\n Shows info about current lfg queues.'),(434,'Command: lfg clean','Syntax: .flg clean\n Cleans current queue, only for debugging purposes.'),(435,'Command: lfg options','Syntax: .lfg options [new value]\n Shows current lfg options. New value is set if extra param is present.'),(436,'Command: list','Syntax: .list $subcommand\nType .list to see the list of possible subcommands or .help list $subcommand to see info on subcommands'),(437,'Command: list creature','Syntax: .list creature #creature_id [#max_count]\r\n\r\nOutput creatures with creature id #creature_id found in world. Output creature guids and coordinates sorted by distance from character. Will be output maximum #max_count creatures. If #max_count not provided use 10 as default value.'),(438,'Command: list item','Syntax: .list item #item_id [#max_count]\r\n\r\nOutput items with item id #item_id found in all character inventories, mails, auctions, and guild banks. Output item guids, item owner guid, owner account and owner name (guild name and guid in case guild bank). Will be output maximum #max_count items. If #max_count not provided use 10 as default value.'),(439,'Command: list object','Syntax: .list object #gameobject_id [#max_count]\r\n\r\nOutput gameobjects with gameobject id #gameobject_id found in world. Output gameobject guids and coordinates sorted by distance from character. Will be output maximum #max_count gameobject. If #max_count not provided use 10 as default value.'),(440,'Command: list auras','Syntax: .list auras\nList auras (passive and active) of selected creature or player. If no creature 